
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `ipcs` etela'at raje' be vasayel ertebati bein process-ha (IPC) dar system, mesle shared memory, message queues va semaphore-ha neshan midahad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `ipcs -q`  --> ✉️ Namayesh message queue-ha
    🔹 `ipcs -m`  --> 🧠 Namayesh shared memory segment-ha
    🔹 `ipcs -s`  --> 🚦 Namayesh semaphore-ha
    🔹 `ipcs -a`  --> 👁️‍🗨️ Namayesh hameye vasayel IPC

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ ipcs

    🔹 Namayesh etela'at kholase raje' be hameye vasayel IPC

    $ ipcs -m

    🔹 Namayesh etela'at raje' be shared memory segment-ha

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ ipcs -q

    🔹 Message queue-haye fa'al dar system ra ba etela'at mored niaz neshan midahad, mesle ID va owner-ha.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `ipcs` command displays information about inter-process communication (IPC) facilities in the system, such as shared memory, message queues, and semaphores.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `ipcs -q`  --> ✉️ Show message queues
    🔹 `ipcs -m`  --> 🧠 Show shared memory segments
    🔹 `ipcs -s`  --> 🚦 Show semaphores
    🔹 `ipcs -a`  --> 👁️‍🗨️ Show all IPC facilities

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ ipcs

    🔹 Displays summary information about all IPC facilities

    $ ipcs -m

    🔹 Displays information about shared memory segments

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ ipcs -q

    🔹 Shows the active message queues in the system with relevant information such as their ID and owner.
